1 Git vs Svn
What are the differences between git and svn?
git is more local based, where the majority it not all of the data is on your computer. SVN is more centralized, where all of the data is more on one super server.

2 Commiting to svn
How are commits handled in svn?
commits are handled by having it upload directly to the server rather than having it on your local device first and then uploading it to the server like you would with git.

3 Checking out svn
How are check outs performed in svn?
It gets a working copy from the repository

4 Bring me my .svn!
How do you create the local working environment with svn (the .svn directory)?
you create the directory, go into the directory and then use svn admin create to create it.

5 Adding to the chaos
How do you add files to the repository?
you use svn add * to add all of the files in your current directory and then use svn mv to move them into a different folder.


