How are branches handled in svn?
branches are different directories

7 or maybe a forest
How many branches can you have at any given time?
Limitless

8 Working copy
What does your local copy of a repository look like with svn?
it looks like a long list of branches from the trunk with all of my commits.

9 Status
How do you check the status of the files you are presently working on?
svn status

10 Life of a branch
How long are branches in svn supposed to exist?
limitless

11 Taping it together
How do you merge branches?
svn merge

12 We see a need!
Why was svn created?
to fix the bugs and supplied some missing features in CVS

13 A day in the life of svn
What is a typical svn workflow?
create repository online or on a centralized server, connect working repository to local device, begin working on project, commit whenever needed.

14 What were they thinking?!
What was the design criteria for svn?
to fix bugs and provide features that were not available on CVS

